{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"It seems to work [here](https:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/webgl_postprocessing_sao.html) with the following setup:\r\n```javascript\r\ncomposer = new THREE.EffectComposer( renderer );\r\n\r\nrenderPass = new THREE.RenderPass( scene, camera );\r\ncomposer.addPass( renderPass );\r\n\r\nsaoPass = new THREE.SAOPass( scene, camera, false, true );\r\nsaoPass.renderToScreen = true;\r\ncomposer.addPass( saoPass );\r\n```\r\nWhat is different in your application from the example's code?","created_at":"2018-02-01T19:49:41.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222#issuecomment-362381394","id":362381394,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2MjM4MTM5NA==","updated_at":"2018-02-01T19:49:54.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/362381394","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"yeah sure the \"normal\" way works like intendend. \r\n\r\nBut I have one problem. When drawing Lines\/LineSegments and draw them via RenderPass (or a custom one) into a framebuffer I have problem with AA. I can use SMAA, FXAA or similar but the results will be way worse than when drawing lines directly on the canvas and not into an FBO.\r\n\r\nSo my intention was that I draw ALL STUFF (background, lines, model) directly on canvas, so the lines are like I want them to be. And with my change, I suggested, everything works fine because the SAO is simply put over my rendered stuff. But with the current implementation 'NoBlending' material clean away my previous rendered stuff on the canvas.\r\nBelow some images for better understanding of my problem ;) \r\n\r\nLike I want it to be (with my changes and everything rendered directly canvas):\r\n![1](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/22448974\/35719813-74eebfb4-07eb-11e8-9626-10bde47060f8.png)\r\nThe \"normal\" way (rendering to FBO), see the ugly lines:\r\n![2](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/22448974\/35719811-74c4bb24-07eb-11e8-9f4e-65a5d0ec6cc3.png)\r\nThe \"normal\" way with applied SMAA, still ugly lines:\r\n![3](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/22448974\/35719812-74daef52-07eb-11e8-8325-7e7a59064813.PNG)\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2018-02-02T06:37:41.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222#issuecomment-362499987","id":362499987,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2MjQ5OTk4Nw==","updated_at":"2018-02-02T06:37:41.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/362499987","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/22448974?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/cnspaha","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyNDQ4OTc0","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"cnspaha","type":"User","id":22448974,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I understand your use case. But with this change `SAOPass` would behave differently compared to other passes in the repo. I'm a little bit concerned about the PR's consistence...","created_at":"2018-02-02T13:20:33.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222#issuecomment-362584320","id":362584320,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2MjU4NDMyMA==","updated_at":"2018-02-02T13:20:33.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/362584320","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> the SAOPass renders the readBuffer (which can be empty) \r\n\r\nCan you please elaborate?\r\n\r\nAlso can you provide live links of your examples?","created_at":"2018-02-03T18:22:30.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222#issuecomment-362842278","id":362842278,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2Mjg0MjI3OA==","updated_at":"2018-02-03T18:22:30.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/362842278","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@Mugen87 \r\nI understand your concerns. But isn't there anything we could do? The current behaviour just doesn't seem right to me..\r\nhmm..\r\nprobably something like this?\r\nSo we would only \"clear\" the previous canvas with ```THREE.NoBlending``` if the clear property is ```true```.\r\n```javascript\r\n\r\n\t\t\/\/ Rendering readBuffer first when rendering to screen\r\n\t\tif ( this.renderToScreen ) {\r\n                        if ( this.clear === true ) {\r\n                            this.materialCopy.blending = THREE.NoBlending;\r\n                        } else {\r\n                            this.materialCopy.blending = THREE.NormalBlending;\r\n                        }\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\tthis.materialCopy.uniforms[ 'tDiffuse' ].value = readBuffer.texture;\r\n\t\t\tthis.materialCopy.needsUpdate = true;\r\n\t\t\tthis.renderPass( renderer, this.materialCopy, null );\r\n\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n@WestLangley \r\nyeah, just prepared a little example\r\nhttps:\/\/jsfiddle.net\/s3rjfcc3\/12\/\r\nas you can see, you only see the green cube+SAO but the red cube is also rendered but overwritten\/cleared by the SAOPass, see images below.\r\n\r\nIn this example the readbuffer isn't empty, it's the green cube. But if it would be empty (no ```THREE.RenderPass```) you would only see black.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n    function animate() {\r\n      requestAnimationFrame(animate);\r\n      renderer.render(scene2, camera); \/\/ rendering of red cube to screen\/canvas\r\n\r\n      composer.render(scene, camera); \/\/ rendering of green cube + SAO to screen\/canvas\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat I expect:\r\n![1](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/22448974\/35790714-142ae670-0a44-11e8-9541-e81832c6dc72.PNG)\r\nWhat I get:\r\n![2](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/22448974\/35790715-144b309c-0a44-11e8-92a3-813ff79c0ca2.PNG)\r\n\r\nSpector.js:\r\nleft side is with my changes, right side without my changes:\r\n![3](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/22448974\/35790713-141067e6-0a44-11e8-9ffe-3cce0cf2b675.PNG)\r\nyou can see, on the left side the SAOPass is being blended with the previous rendered red cube => ```THREE.NormalBlending```, on the right side its ```THREE.NoBlending```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2018-02-05T06:19:28.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222#issuecomment-362991955","id":362991955,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2Mjk5MTk1NQ==","updated_at":"2018-02-05T10:28:37.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/362991955","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/22448974?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/cnspaha","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyNDQ4OTc0","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"cnspaha","type":"User","id":22448974,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"```javascript\r\nrenderer.render(scene2, camera); \/\/ rendering of red cube to screen\/canvas\r\ncomposer.render(scene, camera); \/\/ rendering of green cube + SAO to screen\/canvas\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat is not how `EffectComposer` was designed to be used.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\ncomposer = new THREE.EffectComposer( renderer );\r\n\r\nrenderPass = new THREE.RenderPass( scene2, camera );\r\ncomposer.addPass( renderPass );\r\n\r\nrenderPass = new THREE.RenderPass( scene, camera );\r\nrenderPass.clear = false;\r\ncomposer.addPass( renderPass );\r\n```","created_at":"2018-02-05T16:38:54.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222#issuecomment-363141864","id":363141864,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2MzE0MTg2NA==","updated_at":"2018-02-05T16:38:54.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/363141864","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@WestLangley \r\nyeah I know how it SHOULD be used, but as stated in my second post, if I use it like this the lines just look very bad... so I tried to render everything on screen instead. but when I set ```renderToScreen=true``` on every pass, the lines will look fine, but then the SAOPass cleans the canvas (with its content) with ```THREE.NoBlending```  before rendering the SAO on Top of it.\r\n\r\n@Mugen87 \r\ndo you get my problem here? and understand why the \"way it should be used\" doesn't work for me?","created_at":"2018-02-06T06:23:02.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222#issuecomment-363323197","id":363323197,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13222","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2MzMyMzE5Nw==","updated_at":"2018-02-06T07:16:27.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/363323197","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/22448974?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/cnspaha","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyNDQ4OTc0","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"cnspaha","type":"User","id":22448974,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_asso